<br/>
Robert Runcie is an organizational leader and entrepreneur accomplished in driving change and results in school districts and other large, complex enterprises including government, utilities, and transportation sectors. He provides advisory and consulting services to improve the impact of school districts, education organizations and private companies in accelerating equity and excellence in public schools. He is also a professional leadership coach who supports superintendents and senior leaders of K-12 public school districts.

Robert Runcie has blended his two decades of private sector technology, management consulting and entrepreneurship expertise with 18 years of leadership in urban public schools to deliver innovation, organizational and systems change, and improved student outcomes. Runcie is nationally renowned and has been recognized as “Superintendent of the Year” by the following organizations: Florida Association of District School Superintendents, National Alliance of Black School Educators, Association of Latino Administrators and Superintendents, and Florida Consortium of Public Charter Schools.
